, form and structure, rhythm and movement, and language and imagery are inseparable. The book integrates essays, artistic statements, in-depth conversations, the script of Night Passage, movie stills, photos, and sketches.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDigital cinematography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh1 aBourdier, Jean-Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHohenberger, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinh-ha, Trinh T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNelund, Sidse, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReitsamer, Rosa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRowley, Alison, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZabunyan, Elvan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311071183740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822377320zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822377320423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822377320/original  a978-3-11-071183-7  Duke University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles